chav1961.purelib.fsys

Class FileSystemOnXMLReadOnly

  • java.lang.Object
    • chav1961.purelib.fsys.AbstractFileSystem
      • chav1961.purelib.fsys.FileSystemOnXMLReadOnly
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FileSystemInterface, Closeable, AutoCloseable, Cloneable

    public class FileSystemOnXMLReadOnly
extends AbstractFileSystem

    This class implements the file system interface on the XML gile content.

    Content of XML is interpreted as directory and file tree. 'Directory' is any tag containing other tags or not containing any text content. Use <tag .../> tag's syntax to avoid any text content for the terminal 'directory'.

    The main usability of the file system is to use it as a tree to mount other file systems on it.

    This class is not thread-safe.

    Since:
    0.0.1
    Author:
    Alexander Chernomyrdin aka chav1961
    See Also:
    FileSystemInterface, JUnit tests
